s an extremely influential role model for Hitler, and Hitler continued to back Mussolini even after he rose to power and the "Duce" became dependent on his support. Hitler and Mussolini remained political friends until the very end. This book sheds new light on this unique relationship.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 0aRole modelsvCase studies. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zGermany. 4aAchse Berlin-Rom. 4aBerlin–Rome Axis. 4aDrittes Reich. 4aFaschismus. 4aFascism. 4aItalien. 4aItaly. 4aThird Reich. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2017z9783110547764oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831105270870 cprintz978311052646240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311052975340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110529753423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110529753.jpg  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DEGb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017